sampleTexts.paragraph: Man is a word of Greek origin which we can translate as love of mankind, humanitarianism or benevolence. Kant said that philanthropy must be thought of practically, and not as love, which would be an inclination related to feelings, or compassion. Philanthropy is expressed by acting. A philanthropist is a person who enjoys the wellbeing of another person, regardless of his or her own inclinations, simply for the very wellbeing that the other person is enjoying. He or she feels good if others feel good. A person who feels good only when others feel bad is called a misanthropist. A self-centred person is one who does not care how other people feel, but only cares about how he or she feels. A person who avoids people because he or she does not find any satisfaction in socialising with them, although he or she might wish good to everyone, is called an aesthetic misanthropist, and his or her evasiveness anthropophobia.
